In a large resealable plastic bag, pour 1/2 cup Lawrys(R) Teriyaki Marinade with Pineapple Juice over pork; turn to coat. Close bag and marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes. In another large resealable plastic bag, add 1/4 cup marinade, pineapple, onion and green pepper; toss to coat, then set aside. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Remove pork and vegetables from marinades, discarding marinades. In 13x9-inch roasting pan, arrange pork and vegetables. Roast, brushing occasionally with remaining 1/4 cup marinade, 30 minutes or until done. Slice pork and serve with pineapple, onion, peppers and Shedds Country Crock(tm) Side Dishes Limited Edition Deluxe Mashed Sweet Potatoes.